WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:19.102 --> 00:00:20.478 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
This, ladies and gentlemen,

00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:23.356 position:50% align:center
is what a nervous
breakdown looks like

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:27.569 position:50% align:center
when the one you're crushing on
is avoiding you like the plague.

00:00:35.201 --> 00:00:36.578 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:39.789 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Even his sister
puts two and two together.

00:00:39.873 --> 00:00:43.418 position:50% align:center
I mean, petal-picking
is a pretty dead giveaway.

00:00:43.501 --> 00:00:44.669 position:50% align:center
Hey. What's up?

00:00:44.753 --> 00:00:46.338 position:50% align:center
[KEI grunts]

00:00:49.966 --> 00:00:51.509 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
But, she chooses to ignore it

00:00:51.593 --> 00:00:55.055 position:50% align:center
and acts as if she doesn't care,
resisting the temptation to

00:00:55.138 --> 00:00:58.767 position:50% align:center
grill him for all the
nitty-gritty details.

00:01:00.143 --> 00:01:03.897 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Why, you ask?
Because Kei Shirogane

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:07.067 position:50% align:center
is a mother flippin' <i>tsundere</i> !

00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:38.867 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
C'mon, Kei.

00:02:38.950 --> 00:02:40.493 position:50% align:center
I thought you said you
weren't gonna drink juice

00:02:40.577 --> 00:02:42.662 position:50% align:center
at dinner anymore.

00:02:42.746 --> 00:02:44.205 position:50% align:center
[KEI]
Hmph.

00:02:44.289 --> 00:02:47.792 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI, PAPA SHIROGANE] Munch,
munch. Munch, munch, munch.

00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:54.341 position:50% align:center
Stop being so picky and
eat your green peppers.

00:02:55.633 --> 00:02:58.345 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] That was fast. Did you
scarf down your manners, too,

00:02:58.428 --> 00:02:59.846 position:50% align:center
or did you just
forget to say thank you

00:02:59.929 --> 00:03:00.764 position:50% align:center
and put your dishes in the--?

00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:02.724 position:50% align:center
Shut up!

00:03:02.807 --> 00:03:04.601 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The Shirogane Family!

00:03:04.684 --> 00:03:06.394 position:50% align:center
The father doesn't
have a steady job

00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:08.355 position:50% align:center
and they live in
a 50,000 yen apartment

00:03:08.438 --> 00:03:11.232 position:50% align:center
that's a 20-minute walk
from Sangenjaya Station.

00:03:11.316 --> 00:03:14.736 position:50% align:center
There was a Missus Shirogane,
but she ran off with her lover.

00:03:14.819 --> 00:03:16.154 position:50% align:center
The father's factory going bust

00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:18.615 position:50% align:center
was the icing on this
crappy cake of events.

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:19.908 position:50% align:center
On top of their hardships,

00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:21.868 position:50% align:center
Kei feels her
overprotective big brother

00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:23.536 position:50% align:center
treats her like a little kid.

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:24.913 position:50% align:center
You're not walking out of
this apartment till you...

00:03:24.996 --> 00:03:26.456 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] And the more
she pushes him away,

00:03:26.539 --> 00:03:28.249 position:50% align:center
the louder he seems to nag.

00:03:28.333 --> 00:03:30.752 position:50% align:center
Nag, nag, nag, nag, nag, nag!

00:03:30.835 --> 00:03:32.504 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Thus, their communication

00:03:32.587 --> 00:03:35.298 position:50% align:center
is in a continuous
downward spiral!

00:03:35.382 --> 00:03:37.050 position:50% align:center
But now that Kei
is dying to know

00:03:37.133 --> 00:03:39.386 position:50% align:center
the details of her
brother's romantic life,

00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:42.597 position:50% align:center
her curiosity is slowly
eating away at her.

00:03:42.681 --> 00:03:44.933 position:50% align:center
She can't be obvious
about it, though.

00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.644 position:50% align:center
What? I wanna hear
everything there is to tell!

00:03:47.727 --> 00:03:49.437 position:50% align:center
I mean this girl could
be my sister-in-law!

00:03:49.521 --> 00:03:52.941 position:50% align:center
Tell me! Tell me! Tell me!
Tell me! Tell me! Tell me!

00:03:53.024 --> 00:03:54.275 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
To appear too concerned

00:03:54.359 --> 00:03:55.944 position:50% align:center
is simply out of the question.

00:03:56.027 --> 00:03:57.779 position:50% align:center
She doesn't need that
kind of humiliation.

00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:59.614 position:50% align:center
So how can she force
her brother to dish

00:03:59.698 --> 00:04:01.741 position:50% align:center
while maintaining
her aloof persona?

00:04:01.825 --> 00:04:05.328 position:50% align:center
Her brother isn't the only
one in the family with brains.

00:04:05.412 --> 00:04:07.706 position:50% align:center
[KEI]
What's this?

00:04:07.789 --> 00:04:09.332 position:50% align:center
Picking petals?

00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:10.333 position:50% align:center
That's creepy.

00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:13.586 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The verbal abuse tactic!

00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:14.462 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI grunts]

00:04:14.546 --> 00:04:16.339 position:50% align:center
You must be brokenhearted.

00:04:16.423 --> 00:04:19.384 position:50% align:center
So how exactly did she dump you?

00:04:19.467 --> 00:04:20.885 position:50% align:center
Just leave me alone.

00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:22.554 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:29.144 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI, KEI gasping]

00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:31.896 position:50% align:center
Hey, kids. I'm home.

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:32.897 position:50% align:center
Hi, Dad.

00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:34.190 position:50% align:center
Welcome back.

00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:36.151 position:50% align:center
Thanks.

00:04:36.234 --> 00:04:37.736 position:50% align:center
Hm? Flower petals?

00:04:37.819 --> 00:04:39.863 position:50% align:center
What's this?

00:04:39.946 --> 00:04:43.366 position:50% align:center
So, do you have a crush
on someone, Miyuki?

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:47.078 position:50% align:center
I don't. It's not
like that at all.

00:04:47.162 --> 00:04:48.371 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE]
Sure.

00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:49.956 position:50% align:center
Wanna talk it out?

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:53.084 position:50% align:center
A major part of being a father
is listening to your children.

00:04:53.168 --> 00:04:54.753 position:50% align:center
Tell sugar daddy what's wrong.

00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:58.131 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Please don't call
yourself that ever again.

00:04:58.214 --> 00:05:01.009 position:50% align:center
Fine. I guess I'll tell you.

00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:03.887 position:50% align:center
I thought things were going
pretty well with this one girl,

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:07.015 position:50% align:center
but she's been
avoiding me recently.

00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:08.433 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
I also noticed she's been acting

00:05:08.516 --> 00:05:11.770 position:50% align:center
more friendly than usual
with this other guy I know.

00:05:11.853 --> 00:05:14.272 position:50% align:center
Did she start hating
me for some reason?

00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:16.441 position:50% align:center
I have no clue
how she's feeling.

00:05:16.524 --> 00:05:18.735 position:50% align:center
Hey, what's with the face?

00:05:18.818 --> 00:05:20.362 position:50% align:center
This is tougher than I thought.

00:05:20.445 --> 00:05:22.405 position:50% align:center
Young love's so vexing.

00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:23.531 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
I thought you wanted to listen,

00:05:23.615 --> 00:05:25.033 position:50% align:center
not sit here and mock me!

00:05:25.116 --> 00:05:26.284 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE gasps]
Hold on.

00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:27.535 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:27.619 --> 00:05:30.663 position:50% align:center
My own wife's avoided
me for seven years.

00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:33.708 position:50% align:center
And I highly suspect she's
with a younger man these days.

00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:35.293 position:50% align:center
I know first hand how you feel.

00:05:35.377 --> 00:05:37.837 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Do me a favor and leave
your relationship out of this!

00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.465 position:50% align:center
Get a grip and sign
the divorce papers already!

00:05:40.548 --> 00:05:43.677 position:50% align:center
For better or for worse,
I still care for my wife.

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:45.136 position:50% align:center
[KEI, MIYUKI grunt]

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:48.098 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah. The sports
festival's coming up.

00:05:48.181 --> 00:05:49.683 position:50% align:center
It's no secret:

00:05:49.766 --> 00:05:51.976 position:50% align:center
Girls go crazy over
boys who run fast.

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:53.395 position:50% align:center
Show her what you can do.

00:05:53.478 --> 00:05:55.146 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
We're not in grade school!

00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:56.523 position:50% align:center
Forget it.

00:05:56.606 --> 00:05:58.775 position:50% align:center
You say you know how I feel,
but you have no clue!

00:05:58.858 --> 00:06:01.444 position:50% align:center
--[KEI] Before you go...
--[MIYUKI gasps]

00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:03.988 position:50% align:center
...if a girl you get along
with is suddenly avoiding you,

00:06:04.072 --> 00:06:07.283 position:50% align:center
there's still a possibility
that she likes you.

00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:09.035 position:50% align:center
What makes you say that?

00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:10.453 position:50% align:center
[KEI]
'Cause if she likes you,

00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:12.372 position:50% align:center
the thought of having
a normal conversation with you

00:06:12.455 --> 00:06:14.332 position:50% align:center
probably makes her
feel embarrassed.

00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:16.042 position:50% align:center
It happens more
often than you'd think.

00:06:16.126 --> 00:06:18.378 position:50% align:center
Just give her
a little more time.

00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:20.630 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE gasps]

00:06:20.714 --> 00:06:23.049 position:50% align:center
So it's a fairly
common occurrence?

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:27.178 position:50% align:center
Thanks, I appreciate
the insight.

00:06:27.262 --> 00:06:30.598 position:50% align:center
Yeah, well, I'm gonna
go take a bath.

00:06:30.682 --> 00:06:31.766 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Uh...

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:32.726 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI sighs]

00:06:32.809 --> 00:06:35.395 position:50% align:center
[door opens, closes]

00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:37.564 position:50% align:center
[KEI sighs]

00:06:37.647 --> 00:06:39.065 position:50% align:center
What just happened?

00:06:39.149 --> 00:06:42.110 position:50% align:center
Was I talking to my
brother or someone else?

00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:49.409 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:52.579 --> 00:06:54.748 position:50% align:center
[BOTH grunt]

00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:02.088 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:02.922 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
President.

00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:04.924 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:05.008 --> 00:07:08.553 position:50% align:center
Would you walk with
me to the council room?

00:07:10.805 --> 00:07:13.433 position:50% align:center
Sounds good. Let's go.

00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:20.398 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Results for today's
battle: Shirogane wins.

00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:31.701 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:07:57.894 --> 00:07:59.771 position:50% align:center
[snarls]

00:07:59.854 --> 00:08:02.565 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:08.113 position:50% align:center
Like my finishing move?

00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:09.489 position:50% align:center
[growls] You liar!

00:08:09.572 --> 00:08:12.409 position:50% align:center
You lied to me again and
I actually believed you!

00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:13.993 position:50% align:center
Whatever that was,
it wasn't dancing!

00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:15.995 position:50% align:center
You looked like you were
feeling excruciating pain,

00:08:16.079 --> 00:08:17.539 position:50% align:center
not the music!

00:08:17.622 --> 00:08:19.082 position:50% align:center
I just wanted the demon that
was inside of you to come out!

00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:21.751 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The Japanese folk song, "Soran"!

00:08:21.835 --> 00:08:23.545 position:50% align:center
When it was decided
the second-year students

00:08:23.628 --> 00:08:25.463 position:50% align:center
would do the famed dance
for the sports festival,

00:08:25.547 --> 00:08:27.966 position:50% align:center
Shirogane was nothing
short of confident.

00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:30.885 position:50% align:center
His confidence is what
made Fujiwara worry, though.

00:08:30.969 --> 00:08:33.888 position:50% align:center
And her worries were justified
by the nightmare that ensued.

00:08:33.972 --> 00:08:35.432 position:50% align:center
Long story short,

00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:38.351 position:50% align:center
she once again got suckered
into being his personal coach.

00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:42.564 position:50% align:center
[grunting] Yeah?

00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:43.898 position:50% align:center
Not quite there.

00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:46.443 position:50% align:center
Remember, dance is more
than imitating the moves.

00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:48.445 position:50% align:center
You gotta express yourself!

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:53.324 position:50% align:center
See this fish? It was probably
caught thanks to the soran song.

00:08:53.408 --> 00:08:54.743 position:50% align:center
Men living on the sea.

00:08:54.826 --> 00:08:55.952 position:50% align:center
It's beautiful!

00:08:56.036 --> 00:08:58.246 position:50% align:center
Be the fish struggling
for its life!

00:08:58.329 --> 00:08:59.622 position:50% align:center
And don't forget the net!

00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:01.207 position:50% align:center
You need to feel the weight
of dragging it back in!

00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:02.917 position:50% align:center
You serious right now?!

00:09:03.001 --> 00:09:04.252 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
To be a professional dancer,

00:09:04.336 --> 00:09:06.212 position:50% align:center
you have to understand
where the moves come from!

00:09:06.296 --> 00:09:09.299 position:50% align:center
But I never said I wanted
to be a pro to begin with!

00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:11.259 position:50% align:center
Just learning the
moves is good enough.

00:09:11.343 --> 00:09:13.219 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
"Good enough"?

00:09:16.723 --> 00:09:18.475 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA screams]
This royally sucks!

00:09:18.558 --> 00:09:20.393 position:50% align:center
Your attitude is as
awful as your skills,

00:09:20.477 --> 00:09:22.479 position:50% align:center
and I get stuck
teaching you every time!

00:09:22.562 --> 00:09:23.938 position:50% align:center
Well, it all stops here!

00:09:24.022 --> 00:09:26.274 position:50% align:center
If you ever need help again,
don't come running to me!

00:09:26.358 --> 00:09:27.609 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA screams]

00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:29.903 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:31.946 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI sighs]

00:09:32.030 --> 00:09:34.824 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I can see how
coaching me would be stressful.

00:09:34.908 --> 00:09:37.660 position:50% align:center
But I can still do this,
even without her.

00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:40.330 position:50% align:center
Feel the weight of the net.

00:09:40.413 --> 00:09:42.123 position:50% align:center
Imagine dragging it back in.

00:09:42.207 --> 00:09:45.460 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Hey, there. Practicing
the dance for the festival?

00:09:45.543 --> 00:09:47.003 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI gasps]

00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:49.673 position:50% align:center
You know, I'm no expert, but
I can give you some pointers.

00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:52.008 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
And I get to touch him!

00:09:52.092 --> 00:09:53.009 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:09:53.093 --> 00:09:54.552 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:09:54.636 --> 00:09:57.889 position:50% align:center
Take the "throw it out"
part for example.

00:09:57.972 --> 00:09:59.766 position:50% align:center
Now, puff out your chest.

00:09:59.849 --> 00:10:02.352 position:50% align:center
And take your hips and
lower them down like this.

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.521 position:50% align:center
It looks much better this way.

00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:05.980 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:10:06.064 --> 00:10:08.608 position:50% align:center
Also...

00:10:08.692 --> 00:10:09.943 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:13.196 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
What's going on in here? Hmm?

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:16.449 position:50% align:center
She's teaching
you now? How sweet!

00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:21.788 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah! Kaguya has experience
dancing on an actual stage!

00:10:21.871 --> 00:10:24.416 position:50% align:center
Wow. How lucky!

00:10:24.499 --> 00:10:26.751 position:50% align:center
Please, don't let me stop you.

00:10:26.835 --> 00:10:29.004 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
I get the feeling you're upset.

00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:30.672 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Why would I be upset?

00:10:30.755 --> 00:10:33.174 position:50% align:center
I mean, the ridiculous speed in
which you changed teachers

00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:35.635 position:50% align:center
is something to marvel at,
not get upset about.

00:10:35.719 --> 00:10:38.680 position:50% align:center
By all means, continue.

00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:40.557 position:50% align:center
Dance is a series
of beautiful poses

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:43.101 position:50% align:center
that flow from one
move to the next.

00:10:43.184 --> 00:10:45.603 position:50% align:center
Each move should be made
with a purpose in mind.

00:10:45.687 --> 00:10:47.981 position:50% align:center
She doesn't get it at all.

00:10:48.064 --> 00:10:50.191 position:50% align:center
Yes, Fujiwara? Do you
have something to add?

00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:52.027 position:50% align:center
No, no, you keep going.

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:54.029 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Even your fingers play a part.

00:10:54.112 --> 00:10:57.449 position:50% align:center
So, if you copy the choreography
right down to the fingertips--

00:10:57.532 --> 00:11:00.744 position:50% align:center
A copycat? How nice.

00:11:00.827 --> 00:11:02.245 position:50% align:center
That's twice now.

00:11:02.328 --> 00:11:05.040 position:50% align:center
If you have a problem with
the way I teach, simply say so.

00:11:05.123 --> 00:11:06.916 position:50% align:center
I don't, but...

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.919 position:50% align:center
...you can't deny the raw
feeling of the soran dance.

00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:14.507 position:50% align:center
Definitely not something
you can just copy, right?

00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:16.176 position:50% align:center
If you don't give it
your heart and soul,

00:11:16.259 --> 00:11:18.428 position:50% align:center
it turns out all wrong, right?

00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:20.305 position:50% align:center
The term "heart and
soul" is quite vague

00:11:20.388 --> 00:11:21.890 position:50% align:center
and shouldn't apply to dancing.

00:11:21.973 --> 00:11:23.683 position:50% align:center
What's key is memorizing
the choreography

00:11:23.767 --> 00:11:25.977 position:50% align:center
and training one's body
to efficiently do it.

00:11:26.061 --> 00:11:28.063 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA gasps]

00:11:28.146 --> 00:11:29.647 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Dancers can't
convey the intentions

00:11:29.731 --> 00:11:31.358 position:50% align:center
behind the moves
to the audience.

00:11:31.441 --> 00:11:32.901 position:50% align:center
What winds up translating

00:11:32.984 --> 00:11:35.612 position:50% align:center
is the beautiful performance
if everything is executed well.

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.739 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
You're so wrong!

00:11:37.822 --> 00:11:39.616 position:50% align:center
Though presentation is key,

00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:41.993 position:50% align:center
if it doesn't have love,
then nobody's happy!

00:11:42.077 --> 00:11:43.411 position:50% align:center
Nobody!

00:11:43.495 --> 00:11:45.663 position:50% align:center
You have to teach him the
fun of expressing himself,

00:11:45.747 --> 00:11:47.165 position:50% align:center
or completely butt out!

00:11:47.248 --> 00:11:49.376 position:50% align:center
Or better yet!
I'll just teach him!

00:11:49.459 --> 00:11:51.711 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Your mouth is moving,
but you're not making sense!

00:11:51.795 --> 00:11:53.630 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Whatever! I'm taking him back!

00:11:53.713 --> 00:11:55.173 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Why not let him decide?!

00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.550 position:50% align:center
'Cause I made the
decision for him!

00:11:57.634 --> 00:12:00.261 position:50% align:center
You're acting like
he's a piece of property!

00:12:00.345 --> 00:12:03.056 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Magistrate Echizen
Ooka of Edo was known for

00:12:03.139 --> 00:12:04.891 position:50% align:center
commanding two women
who claimed to be

00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:08.061 position:50% align:center
a child's mother to play
tug-of-war with his body.

00:12:08.144 --> 00:12:10.230 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] The young boy
eventually cried out in pain,

00:12:10.313 --> 00:12:11.731 position:50% align:center
and the woman who
released him first

00:12:11.815 --> 00:12:14.192 position:50% align:center
was deemed worthy
of being his parent.

00:12:14.275 --> 00:12:16.111 position:50% align:center
But in this particular
custody battle,

00:12:16.194 --> 00:12:21.908 position:50% align:center
neither of them are willing
to let the poor boy go!

00:12:21.991 --> 00:12:24.369 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI screams]

00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:30.625 position:50% align:center
The net! That's how it feels!

00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:32.752 position:50% align:center
Soran! Soran!

00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:34.462 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:12:34.546 --> 00:12:37.048 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Throw it out! Pull it in!

00:12:37.132 --> 00:12:38.299 position:50% align:center
Yahoo!

00:12:38.383 --> 00:12:40.677 position:50% align:center
What marvelous soran moves!

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:44.514 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Results for today's
battle: Shirogane wins!

00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.182 position:50% align:center
Be the fishing net.

00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.351 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR whispers]
You are the fishing net!

00:12:48.435 --> 00:12:52.188 position:50% align:center
Soran! Soran! Soran! Soran!

00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:53.898 position:50% align:center
Sora--!

00:12:54.983 --> 00:12:57.444 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
My name is Kobachi Osaragi.

00:12:57.527 --> 00:13:00.196 position:50% align:center
The kanji for Osaragi
means "Great Buddha."

00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:02.532 position:50% align:center
People would do well
to remember this.

00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:04.242 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] As part of the
Disciplinary Committee,

00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:07.912 position:50% align:center
my goal is to keep the school
as moral as I possibly can.

00:13:07.996 --> 00:13:09.414 position:50% align:center
--[MIKO] This is unacceptable!
--[OSARAGI] In other words,

00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:12.584 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] I crack down on
students who break the rules.

00:13:12.667 --> 00:13:14.085 position:50% align:center
However...

00:13:16.296 --> 00:13:17.964 position:50% align:center
Oh! Miko!

00:13:18.048 --> 00:13:19.924 position:50% align:center
The Disciplinary
Committee's here!

00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:21.718 position:50% align:center
Roll 13 or higher to evade!

00:13:21.801 --> 00:13:23.386 position:50% align:center
[KOZUE]
Go!

00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:24.679 position:50% align:center
[GIGAKO]
Yes! Fourteen!

00:13:24.763 --> 00:13:26.222 position:50% align:center
Crisis averted!

00:13:26.306 --> 00:13:27.223 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA, KOZUE, GIGAKO]
Woo! Go us!

00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:28.558 position:50% align:center
We're... still here.

00:13:28.641 --> 00:13:30.018 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA, KOZUE, GIGAKO]
Yay!

00:13:30.101 --> 00:13:32.479 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] What's the Board Game
Club doing outside anyway?

00:13:32.562 --> 00:13:34.814 position:50% align:center
Uh, can't you tell?

00:13:34.898 --> 00:13:37.192 position:50% align:center
We're playing a real-life RPG.

00:13:37.275 --> 00:13:39.152 position:50% align:center
Gotta do our best to
defeat the ancient dragon

00:13:39.235 --> 00:13:40.403 position:50% align:center
that sleeps in the
old school building...

00:13:40.487 --> 00:13:41.905 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Students who
believe they transcend

00:13:41.988 --> 00:13:44.366 position:50% align:center
the rules like this
can be such a headache.

00:13:44.449 --> 00:13:46.159 position:50% align:center
I'm not sure that I understand,

00:13:46.242 --> 00:13:48.036 position:50% align:center
but so long as you don't
cause a disturbance--

00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:51.164 position:50% align:center
Hey! Let's try and use
"warp capsule" here!

00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:52.290 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
No!

00:13:52.374 --> 00:13:54.501 position:50% align:center
Saitama has been
completely obliterated!

00:13:54.584 --> 00:13:55.960 position:50% align:center
[GIGAKO]
What a cruel world!

00:13:56.044 --> 00:13:57.420 position:50% align:center
Man, they're such a pain.

00:13:57.504 --> 00:13:58.922 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:13:59.005 --> 00:14:02.008 position:50% align:center
The amount of common sense
Fujiwara lacks is astounding.

00:14:02.092 --> 00:14:04.386 position:50% align:center
You're one to talk, aren't you?

00:14:04.469 --> 00:14:05.595 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Sorry to burst your bubble,

00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:07.430 position:50% align:center
but you can't take
my game console away.

00:14:07.514 --> 00:14:09.641 position:50% align:center
I'm directly under the
student council room,

00:14:09.724 --> 00:14:12.268 position:50% align:center
which is owned by
the alumni association.

00:14:12.352 --> 00:14:14.187 position:50% align:center
Meaning school
rules don't apply.

00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:16.022 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Is that right?

00:14:16.106 --> 00:14:18.775 position:50% align:center
Then the second you leave,
I can confiscate it.

00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.318 position:50% align:center
[YU yelps]

00:14:20.402 --> 00:14:22.987 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Those two hate each
other with a fiery passion.

00:14:23.071 --> 00:14:24.614 position:50% align:center
Though "passion"
suggests there's something

00:14:24.698 --> 00:14:27.450 position:50% align:center
more between them, so
maybe I should amend that.

00:14:27.534 --> 00:14:29.577 position:50% align:center
Those two just can't
seem to get along.

00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:31.621 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10A]
That guy never learns.

00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:33.623 position:50% align:center
I hear he has no one to talk to.

00:14:33.707 --> 00:14:36.126 position:50% align:center
He acts out so Iino
will pay attention to 'im.

00:14:36.209 --> 00:14:38.294 position:50% align:center
Talk about desperate.

00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.088 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] The first-year
girls at this academy

00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:42.632 position:50% align:center
all seem to detest him.

00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:44.509 position:50% align:center
In his third year
of middle school,

00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:46.386 position:50% align:center
Ishigami apparently
stalked a girl

00:14:46.469 --> 00:14:48.555 position:50% align:center
he had a crush on at the time.

00:14:48.638 --> 00:14:50.265 position:50% align:center
Rumor has it he
went off the deep end

00:14:50.348 --> 00:14:52.851 position:50% align:center
and assaulted her
boyfriend one day.

00:14:52.934 --> 00:14:55.687 position:50% align:center
Suspiciously,
Ishigami elected to never

00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:58.064 position:50% align:center
give his side of the story.

00:14:58.148 --> 00:15:01.026 position:50% align:center
As a result, he was suspended.

00:15:01.109 --> 00:15:02.861 position:50% align:center
The girl transferred
to another school,

00:15:02.944 --> 00:15:05.280 position:50% align:center
and the attacks on Ishigami
in the name of vengeance

00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:07.198 position:50% align:center
for her continue even now.

00:15:07.282 --> 00:15:09.909 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADER SQUAD LEADER 9A]
Team Red! "Hey, Ho!" Ready?

00:15:09.993 --> 00:15:10.994 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
And yet...

00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:12.704 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADERS]
Hey! Ho! Hey! Ho!

00:15:12.787 --> 00:15:16.249 position:50% align:center
Team Red, let's go!
Team Red let's go!

00:15:16.332 --> 00:15:17.917 position:50% align:center
Pump, pump, pump it up!

00:15:18.001 --> 00:15:19.336 position:50% align:center
I'm surprised.

00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.589 position:50% align:center
How can you come to school
and act perfectly fine?

00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:25.300 position:50% align:center
After what happened
with... you know?

00:15:25.383 --> 00:15:27.677 position:50% align:center
Do I look like I'm fine?!

00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:28.636 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADERS]
Hey!

00:15:28.720 --> 00:15:29.471 position:50% align:center
Ho!

00:15:29.554 --> 00:15:32.640 position:50% align:center
Let's go! Let's go!

00:15:32.724 --> 00:15:34.309 position:50% align:center
Hey! Ho!

00:15:34.392 --> 00:15:37.479 position:50% align:center
Let's go!

00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:39.105 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
The Yu Ishigami I've seen

00:15:39.189 --> 00:15:41.232 position:50% align:center
is someone who's
socially awkward.

00:15:41.316 --> 00:15:45.153 position:50% align:center
But who also has a clear
distaste for injustice.

00:15:47.405 --> 00:15:50.241 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] He and Miko
have a lot in common.

00:15:50.325 --> 00:15:51.785 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] The decision
to keep Ishigami from

00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:54.621 position:50% align:center
advancing to the high school
division is going overboard!

00:15:54.704 --> 00:15:56.706 position:50% align:center
The Disciplinary Committee
will not stand for this!

00:15:56.790 --> 00:16:00.710 position:50% align:center
[ADOLPHE] My, what an
interesting conversation.

00:16:00.794 --> 00:16:02.545 position:50% align:center
Care to elaborate?

00:16:02.629 --> 00:16:06.174 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] They're very similar,
yet they still can't get along.

00:16:06.257 --> 00:16:07.676 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADER SQUAD LEADER 9A]
Break!

00:16:09.219 --> 00:16:10.303 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Excuse me.

00:16:10.387 --> 00:16:11.638 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADER SQUAD LEADER 9A]
What's up?

00:16:11.721 --> 00:16:14.015 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] It's about
your new recruit, Ishigami.

00:16:14.099 --> 00:16:15.100 position:50% align:center
[CHEERLEADER SQUAD LEADER 9A]
Yeah?

00:16:15.183 --> 00:16:17.936 position:50% align:center
I, uh, I know that it's weird,

00:16:18.019 --> 00:16:21.481 position:50% align:center
but I don't think he
joined your squad as a joke.

00:16:21.564 --> 00:16:25.318 position:50% align:center
No worries there.
I was well aware of that.

00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:32.450 position:50% align:center
[KOYASU] He's in good hands,
so just leave it to us.

00:16:32.534 --> 00:16:34.411 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] As a member of
the Disciplinary Committee,

00:16:34.494 --> 00:16:36.996 position:50% align:center
it's my duty to keep
students on the correct path,

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:40.834 position:50% align:center
so their school experience
is the best it can be.

00:16:43.461 --> 00:16:45.964 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:16:46.047 --> 00:16:49.300 position:50% align:center
[CROWD singing]

00:16:49.384 --> 00:16:51.302 position:50% align:center
[CROWD]
♪ Soran! Soran! ♪

00:16:51.386 --> 00:16:53.054 position:50% align:center
[music continues playing]

00:16:53.138 --> 00:16:56.224 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I'm fast on my feet
thanks to delivering newspapers.

00:16:56.307 --> 00:16:59.019 position:50% align:center
Not to mention I've
mastered the soran dance!

00:16:59.102 --> 00:17:01.479 position:50% align:center
I feel absolutely unstoppable!

00:17:01.563 --> 00:17:03.857 position:50% align:center
Not a single thing can
bring me down today!

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:05.775 position:50% align:center
Thatta boy, Miyuki!

00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:07.819 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI grunts]

00:17:10.488 --> 00:17:12.574 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
I jinxed myself.

00:17:12.657 --> 00:17:14.159 position:50% align:center
Damn it.

00:17:15.035 --> 00:17:17.203 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10D] Let's give
it up for the soran dance!

00:17:17.287 --> 00:17:20.165 position:50% align:center
[CROWD clapping]

00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:23.168 position:50% align:center
Uh, Dad? What are
you doing here?

00:17:23.251 --> 00:17:24.377 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:17:24.461 --> 00:17:25.754 position:50% align:center
Wasting time.

00:17:25.837 --> 00:17:27.589 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Then get a friggin' job!

00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:29.883 position:50% align:center
[beeping]

00:17:29.966 --> 00:17:32.135 position:50% align:center
Did you take any
pictures of the dance?

00:17:32.218 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50% align:center
Yeah, snagged some
really nice shots.

00:17:35.305 --> 00:17:38.558 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Wow. What a "dad" thing to do.

00:17:38.641 --> 00:17:40.602 position:50% align:center
Or a <i>dirtbag</i> thing to do!

00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:42.187 position:50% align:center
Calm down, son!

00:17:42.270 --> 00:17:45.273 position:50% align:center
He has a shot of my girl because
I asked him to take it for me.

00:17:45.357 --> 00:17:46.566 position:50% align:center
Your girl?

00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:47.859 position:50% align:center
Oh, I get it.

00:17:47.942 --> 00:17:50.236 position:50% align:center
You must be Fujiwara's father.

00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:51.738 position:50% align:center
Nice to meet you.

00:17:51.821 --> 00:17:54.366 position:50% align:center
I'm the president of the Student
Council, Miyuki Shirogane.

00:17:54.449 --> 00:17:57.243 position:50% align:center
Daichi Fujiwara,
at your service.

00:17:57.327 --> 00:17:59.496 position:50% align:center
I'm impressed by how
well-mannered he is.

00:17:59.579 --> 00:18:01.831 position:50% align:center
The result of a fine
upbringing, no doubt.

00:18:01.915 --> 00:18:03.208 position:50% align:center
He's still a kid;

00:18:03.291 --> 00:18:04.918 position:50% align:center
he only started getting
hair down there re--

00:18:05.001 --> 00:18:06.211 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI grunts]

00:18:06.294 --> 00:18:07.879 position:50% align:center
Crap! Shinomiya?

00:18:07.962 --> 00:18:10.173 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] There's no way
in hell she's meeting my dad!

00:18:10.256 --> 00:18:12.634 position:50% align:center
That'd make this
a hundred times worse!

00:18:12.717 --> 00:18:14.135 position:50% align:center
Y'know what, Dad?

00:18:14.219 --> 00:18:16.721 position:50% align:center
You should try our co-op's
curry buns while you're here.

00:18:16.805 --> 00:18:18.640 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:18:18.723 --> 00:18:20.600 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a good idea to me.

00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:23.019 position:50% align:center
I hardly make it out
this way after all.

00:18:23.103 --> 00:18:24.145 position:50% align:center
Nailed it!

00:18:24.229 --> 00:18:26.564 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:18:26.648 --> 00:18:28.066 position:50% align:center
[RED TEAM]
Come on!

00:18:28.149 --> 00:18:29.567 position:50% align:center
Good job!

00:18:29.651 --> 00:18:33.196 position:50% align:center
Let's go! Team Red!

00:18:33.279 --> 00:18:35.699 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
I'm the only one on Team White.

00:18:35.782 --> 00:18:38.410 position:50% align:center
We've got this, team!

00:18:40.328 --> 00:18:43.164 position:50% align:center
Good luck, babe!

00:18:43.248 --> 00:18:44.541 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
We're on different sides,

00:18:44.624 --> 00:18:47.168 position:50% align:center
but I'm gonna cheer
for the president.

00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:53.425 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Good luck, President!

00:18:53.508 --> 00:18:55.260 position:50% align:center
He's so fast!

00:18:55.343 --> 00:18:58.638 position:50% align:center
--[CROWD cheering]
--[starter pistol fires]

00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:03.768 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow!

00:19:03.852 --> 00:19:05.228 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE] So that's
the student council president.

00:19:05.311 --> 00:19:07.689 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:19:07.772 --> 00:19:09.649 position:50% align:center
He's trying way too hard.

00:19:09.733 --> 00:19:13.153 position:50% align:center
Bet he just wants to cover up
what a loser he is. [sighs]

00:19:13.236 --> 00:19:14.529 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] I'm gonna stop
you right there, sir.

00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:15.822 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE]
Hm?

00:19:15.905 --> 00:19:18.116 position:50% align:center
For your information,
President Shirogane

00:19:18.199 --> 00:19:20.493 position:50% align:center
is the perfect representative
for this school.

00:19:20.577 --> 00:19:23.747 position:50% align:center
I'm his second in command,
Kaguya Shinomiya, so

00:19:23.830 --> 00:19:27.125 position:50% align:center
that makes me a better judge of
his character than you, I'd say.

00:19:27.208 --> 00:19:28.793 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya...

00:19:28.877 --> 00:19:31.087 position:50% align:center
Ah. I think I get it.

00:19:31.171 --> 00:19:34.341 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE]
Hmm... Well, in that case...

00:19:35.383 --> 00:19:36.801 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE]
...you have my attention.

00:19:36.885 --> 00:19:40.180 position:50% align:center
So why not tell me all about
your beloved president, eh?

00:19:40.263 --> 00:19:42.223 position:50% align:center
With pleasure!

00:19:42.307 --> 00:19:44.184 position:50% align:center
He has the best grades
in school for starters.

00:19:44.267 --> 00:19:45.977 position:50% align:center
Ooh, whoop-dee frickin' doo.

00:19:46.061 --> 00:19:47.270 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA grunts]

00:19:47.354 --> 00:19:49.356 position:50% align:center
He was elected as
president twice in a row!

00:19:49.439 --> 00:19:50.648 position:50% align:center
[PAPA SHIROGANE]
Yeah, but he only ran against

00:19:50.732 --> 00:19:51.941 position:50% align:center
two or three candidates.

00:19:52.025 --> 00:19:53.651 position:50% align:center
His eyes! They're
so well defined!

00:19:53.735 --> 00:19:56.029 position:50% align:center
Chalk one up for
his mom and dad.

00:19:56.112 --> 00:19:58.406 position:50% align:center
Listen! He's a really
wonderful person, okay?!

